  {
    "question": "What is the Aggregate Method in amortized analysis and how is the amortized cost per operation calculated?",
    "answer": "The Aggregate Method first analyzes the entire sequence of operations, then calculates the amortized cost per operation by dividing the total cost T(n) of n operations by n. It determines an upper bound on the total sequence of n operations, and the amortized cost is T(n)/n, giving an average per operation even if individual operations vary in cost. This method applies the average cost to every operation in the sequence, even if they are of different types."
